FT  18 NOV 94 / Disqualification cases rise by 55%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Disqualification proceedings against company directors are running at 55 per
cent more than at the same time last year, says the insolvency service of
the Department of Trade and Industry.
The increase reflects the service's response to a report from the Commons
public accounts committee that more cases of unfit conduct should be pursued
by the agency.
