FT  18 NOV 94 / London Tecs launch prospectus
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The nine London Training and Enterprise Councils yesterday launched an
economic development prospectus for the capital, calling for flexible skills
training for London's employees.
Mr David Hill, chairman of Aztec, the Tec for south-west London, said
training would have to be more general, rather than targeted at precise job
descriptions. The prospectus said the key issues for London's employers
were: updating skills to combat obsolescence, reskilling to enable staff to
make job changes, upskilling to respond to the rising skills content of many
jobs, multiskilling to enable staff to work across a range of tasks, and
improving generic skills such as customer service and personal relations.
