<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 94 / Nestle to close Norwich factory
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RODERICK ORAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Nestle said yesterday that it will close its Norwich confectionery factory
in two years with the loss of 900 jobs, Roderick Oram writes.
Production will be transferred to several other plants. York, home of the
Rowntree's business Nestle bought in 1988, is apparently the biggest winner.
It is the third tranche of job losses announced by the Swiss multinational
since it completed a review of its UK operations this summer. Job losses so
far total 2,000 out of a UK workforce of 17,000.
Mr David Harris, managing director of Nestle Rowntree, said: 'We need to
reduce our capacity and costs to improve competitiveness so that we can
protect and develop the business for the future.'
