savings, combined with higher volumes flowing from the price cut, should
have a positive effect on profits.
Analysts say Luvs has about 13 per cent of the US disposable nappy market.
Pampers, another Procter &amp; Gamble product, has 26 per cent, Kimberly-Clark's
Huggies 30 per cent, and the rest is taken by private label products.
