<HEADLINE>
FT  17 NOV 94 / The Queen's Speech: Nuclear division wants sale in 1996 -
Privatisation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AEA Technology, whose forthcoming privatisation was confirmed by the
government yesterday, hopes a sale will be made after the financial year
ending March 1996.
The company wants to build a track record following its separation last year
from other divisions at the UK Atomic Energy Authority, whose
responsibilities include overseeing decommissioning and safe handling of
nuclear liabilities.
AEA Technology is a science and engineering business which sells technical,
safety and environmental services and products to industries and governments
throughout the world. It is thought to be worth at least Pounds 200m, has an
annual turnover of Pounds 250m and expects profits this year of Pounds 10m
compared with Pounds 5m last year. The company employs 4,000 people and sees
no likelihood of this declining.
Growth areas include over-seas work, where turnover increased by 40 per cent
last year and is expected to grow this year to about Pounds 60m.
This year is also expected to see a 50 per cent growth in private-sector
business in the UK.
