<HEADLINE>
FT  17 NOV 94 / The Queen's Speech: Scottish bail rules will be tightened
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES BUXTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The criminal justice bill for Scotland will include measures to increase
penalties for people who commit crimes while on bail and make it difficult
or impossible for people convicted of serious offences such as murder or
rape to get bail when charged with a similar offence, James Buxton writes.
The bill will also streamline court procedures in an attempt to reduce the
number of trials adjourned or cancelled at the last minute. Scotland's
unique 'fiscal fine' - a fixed penalty fine similar to a parking ticket -
will be extended to deal with a wider range of minor offences.
The appeal system will be amended so that two judges instead of three will
preside over many appeals against sentences.
